data.title: Terms of Use | Offering Types and Benefits | Autodesk
data.content: Terms of Use | Offering Types and Benefits | Autodesk TERMS OF USE General Terms Special Terms Offering Types & Benefits Acceptable Use Back to top Terms of Use As of May 26, 2023, our Terms of Use have changed. Learn More The Autodesk Terms of Use include the following: General Terms Special Terms Offering Types & Benefits Acceptable Use Offering Types and Benefits Definitions Offering Types Single User Multi User Flex Education Cloud Credits Product-Specific Offering Types Assemble Autodesk Construction Cloud Autodesk Forma Autodesk Fusion Autodesk Informed Design Autodesk Tandem BIM 360 Glue Service and BIM Collaborate / BIM Collaborate Pro Flow Retopology Flow Wedging Fusion Machine Connect Fusion Operations ICMLive and IWLive Pro Info360 InfoAsset Manager (including InfoAsset Mobile and InfoAsset Online) Moldflow Insight XPSWMM Sewer and XPSWMM Complete Plan Benefits Standard Premium Offering Types and Benefits Last updated: June 18, 2025 Capitalized terms not otherwise defined below will have the meaning assigned to them in the General Terms . Offering Benefits may vary depending on the Offering. The Offering Types and Benefits set forth here may be updated from time to time. Notice of updates will be posted on the “Effective Date/Updated" link at the top of this page. Definitions “ Administrator ” or “ Admins ” means personnel who You authorize to use Autodesk user management capabilities to designate Teams and manage access to Offerings and related Offering Benefits by Your Authorized Users assigned to such Teams. There are different types of Administrators that You can designate, including primary, secondary, and SSO Administrators. “ Approved Country ” means a country or jurisdiction listed on the Approved Country List located here: https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/access-use/subscription-offerings . “ Autodesk ID ” means a unique user identification used by Autodesk to identify a specific, unique individual Authorized User. “ Collection ” means two (2) or more Autodesk products bundled together based on industry. “ Desktop Device” means any desktop computer, laptop computer, or virtual machine not accessed through a network connection. “ Electronic Device” means any (i) Desktop Device or (ii) Mobile Device. “Mobile Device” means any smart phone or tablet. “ Non-Approved Country ” means any country or jurisdiction that is not listed on the Approved Country List. “ Offering Benefits ” means the various benefits available for each Offering, including Plan Benefits. Certain Offering Benefits and Plan Benefits are not available for all Offerings. To determine which Offering Benefits and Plan Benefits are available for an Offering, as well as any additional limitations and conditions on access or use of that Offering, see the Documentation for that Offering. “ Offering Types ” means the types of subscription available for each Offering. Certain Offering Types are not available for all Offerings. To determine which Offering Types are available for an Offering, see the Documentation for that Offering. “ Plan Benefits ” means the administrative, customer, technical, and other support provided by Autodesk for certain Offerings. Plan Benefits are not available for all Offerings. To determine which Plan Benefits are available for an Offering, see the Documentation for that Offering. " Premium ” means the Premium plan, wherein Premium Plan Benefits are provided unless otherwise indicated herein. “ Standard ” means the Standard plan, wherein Standard Plan Benefits are provided unless otherwise indicated herein. “ Team ” means a group of unique Authorized Users defined and managed by a given primary Administrator. Offering Types Autodesk offers the following Offering Types: Single User Multi User , which may be described or labeled as “multi-user” or similar Flex Education , and Cloud Credits Each Offering Type, its associated Offering Benefits, and its legal terms and conditions are set forth below. Offering Benefits shall only be available as expressly provided below and, as applicable, in the section titled “Plan Benefits” herein. For Offerings purchased prior to May 18, 2018, and maintenance plans purchased at any time, see here: https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/access-use/subscription-offerings . Special Terms may apply to Your access and use of certain Offerings and Offering Benefits, and such access and use is conditioned on Your agreement to the indemnification included in the Special Terms. Single User Single User supports individuals that seek to use Autodesk products on their own. For any Single User Offering, each Authorized User must be assigned a unique Autodesk ID. The Authorized User must log in using their Autodesk ID to install and/or access each Single User Offering, and no one else may use the same Autodesk ID to access and/or use such Offering. Your Authorized User may concurrently use only one (1) Desktop Device and one (1) Mobile Device at...

<div class="text">
<div id="text-d2e43b4b85" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 ">
  <p class="wd-font-16 wd-mb-12">Last updated: June 18, 2025</p>

</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-828e2f4140" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 ">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Capitalized terms not otherwise defined below will have the meaning assigned to them in the <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/company/terms-of-use/en/general-terms" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="general terms"><b>General Terms</b></a>. Offering Benefits may vary depending on the Offering. The Offering Types and Benefits set forth here may be updated from time to time. Notice of updates will be posted on the “Effective Date/Updated" link at the top of this page.</p>

    <div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="title-e6337476c8">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-20">
    Definitions</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-97ecae0c32" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 ">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Administrator</b>” or “<b>Admins</b>” means personnel who You authorize to use Autodesk user management capabilities to designate Teams and manage access to Offerings and related Offering Benefits by Your Authorized Users assigned to such Teams. There are different types of Administrators that You can designate, including primary, secondary, and SSO Administrators.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Approved Country</b>” means a country or jurisdiction listed on the Approved Country List located here: <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/access-use/subscription-offerings" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="subscription offerings">https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/access-use/subscription-offerings</a><u>.</u></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Autodesk ID</b>” means a unique user identification used by Autodesk to identify a specific, unique individual Authorized User.<br>
</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Collection</b>” means two (2) or more Autodesk products bundled together based on industry.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Desktop Device” </b>means any desktop computer, laptop computer, or virtual machine not accessed through a network connection. </p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Electronic Device” </b>means any (i) Desktop Device or (ii) Mobile Device.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>“Mobile Device”</b> means any smart phone or tablet.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b style="">Non-Approved Country</b>” means any country or jurisdiction that is not listed on the Approved Country List.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Offering Benefits</b>” means the various benefits available for each Offering, including Plan Benefits. Certain Offering Benefits and Plan Benefits are not available for all Offerings. To determine which Offering Benefits and Plan Benefits are available for an Offering, as well as any additional limitations and conditions on access or use of that Offering, see the Documentation for that Offering.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Offering Types</b>” means the types of subscription available for each Offering. Certain Offering Types are not available for all Offerings. To determine which Offering Types are available for an Offering, see the Documentation for that Offering.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Plan Benefits</b>” means the administrative, customer, technical, and other support provided by Autodesk for certain Offerings. Plan Benefits are not available for all Offerings. To determine which Plan Benefits are available for an Offering, see the Documentation for that Offering.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">"<b>Premium</b>” means the Premium plan, wherein Premium Plan Benefits are provided unless otherwise indicated herein.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Standard</b>” means the Standard plan, wherein Standard Plan Benefits are provided unless otherwise indicated herein.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Team</b>” means a group of unique Authorized Users defined and managed by a given primary Administrator.<b></b></p>

</div>

    

</div>

  <div id="offering-types" class="cmp-container wp-parent legal-section ">
    
    <div class="core-container">

  
  
  
  
  <div id="container-5a7c1fe45d" class="cmp-container wd-mb-48 ">
    
    <div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="title-7c5b5034e8">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-20">
    Offering Types</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-95083de1e0" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 ">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Autodesk offers the following Offering Types:<br>
</p>
<ul>
<li style="font-size: 14.0px;"><b>Single User</b>
</li><li style="font-size: 14.0px;"><b>Multi User</b>, which may be described or labeled as “multi-user” or similar
</li><li style="font-size: 14.0px;"><b>Flex</b>
</li><li style="font-size: 14.0px;"><b>Education</b>, and
</li><li style="font-size: 14.0px;"><b>Cloud Credits</b>
</li></ul>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Each Offering Type, its associated Offering Benefits, and its legal terms and conditions are set forth below. Offering Benefits shall only be available as expressly provided below and, as applicable, in the section titled “Plan Benefits” herein.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">For Offerings purchased prior to May 18, 2018, and maintenance plans purchased at any time, see here: <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/access-use/subscription-offerings" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="subscription offering">https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/access-use/subscription-offerings</a>.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><a href="/company/terms-of-use/en/special-terms" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="special terms">Special Terms</a> may apply to Your access and use of certain Offerings and Offering Benefits, and such access and use is conditioned on Your agreement to the indemnification included in the Special Terms.</p>

</div>

    

</div>

    
  </div>


</div>

    
  </div>


</div>
<div class="core-container aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">

  
  
  
  
  <div id="single-user" class="cmp-container legal-section ">
    
    <div class="core-container">

  
  
  
  
  <div id="container-52aa55d206" class="cmp-container wd-mb-48 ">
    
    <div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="title-3ee4370b94">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
    Single User</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-0c97882e22" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 ">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b><i>Single User supports individuals that seek to use Autodesk products on their own.</i></b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">For any Single User Offering, each Authorized User must be assigned a unique Autodesk ID. The Authorized User must log in using their Autodesk ID to install and/or access each Single User Offering, and no one else may use the same Autodesk ID to access and/or use such Offering.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Your Authorized User may concurrently use only one (1) Desktop Device and one (1) Mobile Device at a time to access the Software. For any Collection, Your Authorized User may concurrently use any Software titles in the Collection, but they may use only one (1) Desktop Device and one (1) Mobile Device at a time to do so.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">For purposes of this section only, “access” does not include batch processing, renders, idle usage (i.e., when the Software is open but there is no user input) or similar activities that may run in the background of the Software (“<b>Background Activities</b>”). For the avoidance of doubt, Your Authorized User’s access of the Software to perform Background Activities does not count toward the concurrent use limits set forth in this section. Any Background Activities are subject to reasonable rate limits and technical limitations, which Autodesk has the sole discretion to impose at any time without notice.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You may reassign Your Single User subscription from one (1) individual Authorized User to another individual Authorized User if You follow and complete Autodesk’s policy and process for reassignment and comply with these Terms. This includes, but is not limited to, ensuring that each individual Authorized User has a unique Autodesk ID, and that the single-user subscription is assigned to the Autodesk ID for the individual Authorized User who is actually accessing and using the subscription. If Your Offering is described as "Education Single User," then the terms applicable to that Education Offering can be found in the section titled “Education” herein.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Certain Single User Offerings are not eligible for Premium Plan Benefits.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Single User Global Use Rights</b>. For Single User Offerings, You and Your Authorized Users may use such Offerings globally, subject to the table below. Global use rights are determined by the Territory in which you purchased the Offering. The Territory is identified in the commercial transaction documents applicable to Your purchase. Support while traveling outside the Territory is available according to the support hours for the country and region in which You are traveling.<br>
<br>
<b></b></p>
<table cellspacing="2" cellpadding="8" border="1">
<tbody><tr><td colspan="2" width="638" valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Global Use rights for Single User Offerings</b></p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td width="213" valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Territory</b></p>
</td>
<td width="426" valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Global Use rights</b></p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td width="213" valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Approved Country</p>
</td>
<td width="426" valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You and Your Authorized Users may access and use the Single User Offering worldwide.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td width="213" valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Non-Approved Country</p>
</td>
<td width="426" valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You and Your Authorized Users may access and use the Single User Offering in the Territory, in any other Non-Approved Country, and, if the Authorized User is a resident of a Non-Approved Country, in an Approved Country when traveling there for work for no more than 90 days in a 12-month period.</p>
</td>
</tr></tbody></table>

</div>

    

</div>

    
  </div>


</div>

    
  </div>


</div>
<div class="core-container aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">

  
  
  
  
  <div id="multi-user" class="cmp-container wp-parent legal-section ">
    
    <div class="core-container">

  
  
  
  
  <div id="container-63926aa0e1" class="cmp-container wd-mb-48 ">
    
    <div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="title-915c1bd46c">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
    Multi User</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-d503b70b6d" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 ">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b><i>Multi User supports Teams that seek to use Autodesk products.</i></b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">For any Multi User Offering, Your Authorized Users are limited to: (a) Your individual employees, and (b) Your consultants and contractors, to the extent they work on Your premises and/or on computers and other Electronic Devices owned or leased by You. Your Authorized Users may access and/or use the Offerings solely for Your internal business needs. The number of concurrent Authorized Users may not exceed the maximum number of Authorized Users as specified in Your subscription documentation or other technical limit or subscription limit imposed by Your subscription. Your Authorized Users may access the Offerings via Your local area network (LAN) or virtual private network (VPN), but either such network must use current industry standard security, encryption and protection practices to prevent unauthorized use.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You may (i) install the license server component of the Software to which You have subscribed on an Electronic Device within Your local area network acting as a file server; and (ii) install copies of the corresponding Software on Electronic Devices used by Your Authorized Users.<br>
<br>
<b>Multi User Global Use Rights</b>. For Multi User Offerings, provided that the Territory in which You purchased the Offering was the country in which You reside if You are an individual, or the country in which You are incorporated, chartered or otherwise organized if You are a legal entity (Your “<b>Home Country</b>”), You and Your employees may install and access such Offering outside the Territory on one (1) unique Electronic Device per individual that is traveling – i.e., You or Your employee, respectively. While You or Your employee are located outside the Territory, such Offering may not be copied or transferred to any other Electronic Device or accessed by anyone other than You or Your individual employee while outside the Territory. For Multi User Offerings, Authorized Users other than You or Your employees are not eligible for Global Use rights.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Support while traveling outside the Territory is available according to the support hours for the country and region in which You are traveling.<br>
<br>
For Multi User Offerings, You or Your employees may install and access a copy of a purchased Offering on one (1) Electronic Device located in the Territory but away from Your business site, so long as access and use is only for Your own internal business needs, including but not limited to individual employee training on use of the Offering , including any previous versions You may be entitled to use and any related materials (a “<b>Home Use Copy</b>”). Access to and use of any Home Use Copy is subject to the following conditions: (a) the number of Home Use Copies that You or Your employees install may not exceed the number of seats you have purchased for the Multi User Offering; (b) You must follow the processes and policies set out from time to time by Autodesk for requesting and using a Home Use Copy; (c) You or Your employee may not access or use two (2) or more Multi User Offering seats concurrently (e.g., at Your business site and a Home Use Copy); (d) to access and use the so-called second copy of the Offering, You must receive a Home Use Copy authorization code from Autodesk, and Your right to use a Home Use Copy starts when Autodesk issues you such authorization code and ends on the earlier of termination or expiration of your Multi User subscription or thirteen (13) months from the date Autodesk issued you such authorization code; (e) Home Use Copies are not permitted for Upgrades; (f) in the event of loss, a Home Use Copy will not be replaced or reissued; (g) Autodesk does not provide Support to Home Use Copies; and (h) if the employment of Your employee, who  has a Home Use Copy, terminates, You are responsible for terminating that individual’s access to such Home Use Copy.<br>
<br>
If You acquire a Switched Subscription, You or Your employees may continue to use Home Use Software copies authorized and activated prior to the switch if the same Software is included in the Switched Subscription. If the same Software is not included in the Switched Subscription, You and Your employees must cease using the Home Use Software copies upon switching. For the terms and conditions governing Switched Subscriptions, see here: <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/switched-subscriptions-terms-and-conditions" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="switched subscriptions terms and conditions">https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/switched-subscriptions-terms-and-conditions</a>.</p>

</div>

    

</div>

</div>

  <div id="container-3beeff5059" class="cmp-container wd-mb-48 ">
    
    <div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="title-bd29ee8bc8">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
    
    Flex</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-97aea95f84" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 ">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b><i>Flex enables Authorized Users to access eligible Autodesk products on demand with Tokens</i></b><br>
</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Any Offering eligible for Flex is listed on the Flex Rate Sheet and is known as a “<b>Flex Offering</b>.”<b><i> </i></b>Each Flex Offering is listed in the Flex Rate Sheet. “<b>Flex Rate Sheet</b>” means the current Autodesk document listing Flex Offerings and the applicable number of Tokens required to access and use an Offering as specified in the Flex Rate Sheet. The Flex Rate Sheet can be found here: <a href="http://www.autodesk.com/flexratesheet" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="flex rate sheet">https://www.autodesk.com/flexratesheet</a>. “<b>Token</b>” means the individual unit of measurement that may be applied toward access to and use of Flex Offerings in accordance with the consumption rates shown on the Flex Rate Sheet. A Flex Token is exclusive to Flex and cannot be used in place of tokens, credits or other similar proxies associated with other Offerings. Non-Flex tokens, credits or other similar proxies associated with other Offerings cannot be used for Flex.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">All Flex Offerings have an associated Token Rate (which may be zero in some cases), as specified in the Flex Rate Sheet.<b> </b>“<b>Token Rate</b>” means the rate at which a Flex Offering consumes Tokens when the Flex Offering is first accessed by an Authorized User. For Token Rates measured on a per-day basis, the “day” is the contiguous twenty-four (24)-hour period that begins when an Authorized User first launches the Flex Offering. When an Authorized User launches a Flex Offering, Tokens will be consumed at the applicable Token Rate until the Authorized User exits that Flex Offering.<br>
<br>
<b>Flex Offering Features and Details</b>. For any Flex Offering, You may assign an unlimited number of Authorized Users, but each Authorized User must be registered, set up in Autodesk Account, and assigned to a Team with access to at least one (1) Token Pack. Each of Your Authorized Users may only access and use a Flex Offering on one (1) Electronic Device at a time. “<b>Token Pack</b>” means a specified quantity of Tokens purchased as a unit. You may purchase additional Token Packs at any time, including multiple Token Packs as part of a single purchase or single Token Packs at different points in time. Individual Tokens and partial Token Packs are not available.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Flex Offerings have no fixed contract term. All Tokens expire twelve (12) months from the date of purchase of the Token Pack containing those Tokens. No credit, refund or other accommodation will be provided by Autodesk in connection with Token expiration. You may not sell, sub-license, or otherwise convey Your Tokens. However, You may transfer Your Token Pack to an Affiliated Entity, but Your remaining token balance of such Token Pack must be transferred in full. Such Affiliated Entity’s access and use of the transferred tokens shall be subject to the Terms. The term “<b>Affiliated Entity</b>” as used in this section means, with respect to transferor and transferee entities, the entity that controls, or is controlled by, the other entity, or the parent entity in the case where both transferor and transferee are under common control of such parent entity. For more information, see the compilation of business information regarding the Flex Offering model which may include but is not limited to purchasing or other offering operational rules, requirements, policies or other limitations or conditions, Administrator and Authorized User best practices, and other general information regarding the Flex Offering (“<b>Flex Offering Materials</b>”). Flex Offering Materials can be found here: <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/benefits/flex#faq" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="benefits flex">https://www.autodesk.com/benefits/flex#faq</a> and <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/support/account/admin/plans/flex-access#faq" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="flex faq">https://www.autodesk.com/manageflex#faq</a><br>
<br>
When the Tokens Packs assigned to Authorized Users have been completely consumed and no Tokens remain, those Authorized Users will be ineligible and unauthorized to access and use any Flex Offerings or the associated benefits, including those products that consume zero Tokens. When the Token Packs assigned to an Authorized User has Tokens remaining but in an amount insufficient to satisfy the required Token Rate applicable to a Flex Offering, such Authorized User will be ineligible and unauthorized to access and use any Flex Offering for which there are insufficient Tokens remaining, but they will remain eligible and authorized to access and use any Flex Offering for which sufficient Tokens remain and any Flex Offering that has a zero Token Rate. Autodesk reserves the right, without further notice, to shut off access to and use of Flex Offerings by Your Authorized Users in cases where You have a zero Token balance, insufficient Tokens or nonpayment of invoices when due. If You have an unpaid invoice, Autodesk also may restrict Your ability to purchase additional Token Packs.<br>
<br>
Autodesk may, at any time, add, modify, or eliminate, in whole or in part, any Flex Offering, contents of the Flex Offering Materials or the Token Rates contained in the Flex Rate Sheet. Such additions, modifications, and eliminations will take effect immediately upon publication of a new Flex Rate Sheet or update to Flex Offering Materials, or on such later date as specified in the updated Flex Rate Sheet or Flex Offering Materials.<br>
<br>
<b>Flex Offering Benefits. </b>The Offering Benefits for Flex available to Your Authorized Users will depend on whether those Authorized Users also are assigned to other types of Offerings and, if so, the applicable Plan Benefits of those Offerings.<b></b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">If a Flex Authorized User is not also assigned to any other Offering Type or is additionally assigned to one (1) or more Single User subscriptions on Standard, the Offering Benefits available for that Flex Authorized User will be the same as the benefits available to that Authorized User for Single User subscriptions on Standard, except for reporting, which, for Flex only, will be as described herein in the section titled Flex Usage Reporting and Related Requirements.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">If a Flex Authorized User is also assigned to any other Offering on Premium, then the Flex Offering Benefits for that Authorized User will include Premium Plan Benefits.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Exceptions to the Flex Offering Benefits, if any, will be included in the Flex Offering Materials.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Flex Global Use Rights</b>. For Flex Offerings, whether purchased in an Approved Country or a Non-Approved Country, You and Your Flex Authorized Users may access and use such Flex Offerings worldwide.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Flex Data Collection and Use</b>. Autodesk will monitor use of Flex Offerings by collecting Authorized User Flex Offering usage data, if available, on an ongoing basis. You or Your Administrator, as applicable, will have access to reporting related to such usage data and the associated Token consumption. Autodesk will process this data to generate applicable usage reports, maintain and/or deliver the Flex Offering and related Benefits and assist You or Your reseller with sizing and quoting additional Token purchases. For Flex, Autodesk (a) collects and meters usage data as each Authorized User, assigned by You, consumes Tokens by accessing and using such Offering, (b) provides You with usage data regarding Token consumption, and (c) subtracts Tokens from the total number of Tokens You have available based on the specific Offerings used by Your Authorized Users and the applicable Token consumption rate for each such Offering. Collectively, the foregoing in this section is referred to as the “Flex Data Collection and Use Purposes.” For the avoidance of doubt, the terms in this section titled “Flex Data Collection and Use” do not affect Autodesk‘s right to use personal data received from or on behalf of You that Autodesk processes as a Controller for the purposes described in the Autodesk Privacy Statement, here: <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/privacy-statement" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="privacy statement">https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/privacy-statement</a>.<br>
<br>
<b>Flex Usage Reporting and Related Requirements.</b> You will have access to reporting information related to Flex Token consumption, including Token balance and Token consumption as specified in the Flex Rate Sheet.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">For any Flex usage reporting that You use, You acknowledge and agree that You are responsible for compliance with all requirements under the applicable privacy, data protection and employment laws related to such collection and use of personal data of Your Authorized Users, whether employees, independent contractors, or otherwise, including any applicable requirements related to notice, consent, transfer (including cross-border transfer), disclosure and use, and in particular in connection with the collection and use of types of data described in the section titled “Flex Data Collection and Use”. Without limiting the foregoing, You are specifically responsible for notifying Authorized Users of and/or obtaining their valid consent to collection and use of personal data for the Flex Data Collection and Use Purposes, where such notice and consent are required.</p>

</div>

    

</div>

    
  </div>


</div>

    
  </div>


</div>
<div class="core-container aem-GridColumn aem-GridColumn--default--12">

  
  
  
  
  <div id="education" class="cmp-container wp-parent legal-section ">
    
    <div class="core-container">

  
  
  
  
  <div id="container-6b9d369e77" class="cmp-container wd-mb-48 ">
    
    <div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="title-5219dc749f">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
        Education</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-504fa84629" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 ">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b><i>Certain Autodesk products are available to Students, Faculty, Qualified Educational Institutions, Design Competition Users, and Other Authorized Education Users.</i></b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You must be an Education User to access or use an Education Offering, including any Software licensed as an Education Offering or other Education subscription. To qualify as an Education User, you must be a Student, Faculty, Design Competition User, Qualified Education Institution or Other Authorized Education User, as discussed in this Education Section. You may be required to show proof of eligibility if requested by Autodesk to access or continue to access Education Offerings. Educator Users may only use an Education Offering for purposes related to learning, teaching, or research and development as part of the instructional functions performed by a Qualified Educational Institution or an Other Authorized Education User. Education Users may not access or use the Education Offering for commercial or professional purposes, training classes (including but not limited to classes open to the public), facilities management, or other for-profit purposes. Education Offerings may not be used by the facilities department of a Qualified Educational Institution. Only current Students and Faculty of a Qualified Educational Institution may access and/or use Offerings licensed or subscribed to by a Qualified Educational Institution, and Students and Faculty may be required to use their own individual Autodesk ID to access and/or use certain Offerings.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You are an Education User if you are any of the following: (a) an educational institution that has been accredited by an authorized governmental agency within its applicable local, state, provincial, federal or national government and has the primary purpose of teaching its enrolled students (“<b>Qualified Educational Institution</b>”); (b) an individual person who is an employee or independent contractor working for a Qualified Educational Institution (“<b>Faculty</b>”); (c) an individual person enrolled as a student at a Qualified Educational Institution, who meets the minimum age requirements set by Autodesk to access an Offering here: <a href="https://damassets.autodesk.net/content/dam/autodesk/www/Company/legal-notices-trademarks/education-special-terms/eng-final-minimum-age-requirements-02-03-2022.pdf" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="agre requirement pdf">https://damassets.autodesk.net/content/dam/autodesk/www/Company/legal-notices-trademarks/education-special-terms/eng-final-minimum-age-requirements-02-03-2022.pdf</a> (a “<b>Student</b>”); (d) a Student or other individual who is registered and accepted or otherwise approved by a design competition organizer as an Autodesk-sponsored design competition participant (and, upon request by Autodesk, able to provide proof of such status) or an individual who provides guidance, advice, coaching, or instruction to competitors engaged in competing in an Autodesk-sponsored design competition (and, upon request by Autodesk, able to provide proof of such status) (each a “Design Competition User”), solely for purposes directly related to an Autodesk-sponsored design competition (for a list of Autodesk-sponsored competitions, please see the Autodesk Education Community (or successor site thereto): <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/education/competitions" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="education competitions">https://www.autodesk.com/education/competitions</a>); or (e) an individual user otherwise authorized in writing by Autodesk to access and use an Education Offering (an “<b>Other Authorized Education User</b>”);</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Examples of Qualified Educational Institutions include, without limitation, public or private: (i) middle schools and high schools, (ii) junior colleges, (iii) colleges, universities and technical schools, and (iv) home-school programs which belong to a nationally recognized home-schooling body or are expressly recognized by a local school governing body as an acceptable alternative to an accredited educational institution. The term “Qualified Educational Institution” does not include non-accredited educational institutions; training centers; churches and other places of worship; hospitals, healthcare systems and research laboratories; libraries; and museums ,</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Your entitlement to use any Education Offering commences when we grant You access and ends upon the earlier of (w) the expiration of the term Autodesk specifies for the Education Offering or, if no term is specified, one (1) year thereafter; (x) the date You no longer qualify to use Education Offerings; (y) the date Autodesk discontinues the Education Offering; or (z) upon notice from Autodesk that Your Education Offering access is ending.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You may install copies of the Software You have licensed or subscribed to solely on Electronic Devices owned or controlled by You. You may install Software on up to three (3) Electronic Devices; however, You may only use the Software on one (1) Electronic Device at a time. Likewise, for a Collection, You may install the Software titles in a Collection collectively on up to three (3) Electronic Devices. You may simultaneously use any Software titles in the Collection, provided that any such use is only on one (1) Electronic Device at a time.<br>
<br>
Output and other data created with Education Offerings may contain certain notices and limitations that make the Output and other data usable only in certain circumstances (e.g., only in the education field). If You combine or link any Output or other data created with such Education Offering with other work product or data otherwise created, then such other work product or data may also be affected by these notices and limitations. Autodesk will have no responsibility or liability whatsoever if You or any other person combine or link Outputs created with such Education Offerings with other work product or data otherwise created. In addition, You will not remove, alter, or obscure any such notices or limitations.<br>
<br>
<b>Education Single User</b>. If Your Education Offering is described as “Education Single User,” then You have access to the Autodesk Education plan. For more information about the Education plan, please see here: <span style="color: black;"><a href="https://www.autodesk.com/buying/plans" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="buying plans">https://www.autodesk.com/buying/plans</a></span>.<br>
<br>
If Your Education Offering is described as "Education Single User,” and you are (a) a Student accessing the Education Offering or (b) Faculty accessing the Education Offering solely for your individual use, then You are the Authorized User and you may not assign your subscription to any other person. You must log in using your Autodesk ID to install and/or access each Education Offering, and no one else may access and/or use such Education Offerings using the same Autodesk ID.<br>
<br>
If Your Education Offering is described as “Education Single User,” and you are Faculty managing multiple education single-user subscriptions for a class, cohort, or other group of Students, then (i) You may only assign each subscription to one (1) of Your Authorized Users at a time; (ii) You must verify that each of your Authorized Users is an Education User; (iii) You agree that you will only provide access to Education Users; and (iv) You may administratively reassign Your education single-user subscription from one individual Authorized User to another individual Authorized User if You follow and complete Autodesk’s policy and process for reassignment. Autodesk’s policy and process for reassignment includes, but is not limited to, ensuring that each individual Authorized User has a unique Autodesk ID and that the education single-user subscription is assigned to the Autodesk ID for the unique Authorized User who is actually accessing and using the subscription.<br>
<br>
<b>Educational Multi-seat Stand-alone</b>. If Your Education Offering is described as “Educational Multi-seat Stand-alone,” then You may install copies of the specific release of the Offering designated in the applicable Offering Identification on no more than the permitted number of computers specified in the Offering Identification, and permit access to such copies of the Offering solely by Education Users. The Offering may be installed only on one (1) computer and may not be installed on, or operated, viewed or otherwise accessed from or through any other device (e.g., through a network connection of any kind).<br>
<br>
<b>Educational Network</b>. If Your Education Offering is described as “Educational Network,” then You may install copies of the specific release of the Offering designated in the applicable Offering Identification on a single file server computer and access such Offering on multiple computers on a “<b>Networked Basis</b>” (i.e., a computing environment that includes a computer acting as a file server which allows the Offering installed on such computer to be uploaded and installed to, and operated, viewed or otherwise accessed from, other computers through a local area network (LAN) connection or through a secure virtual private network (VPN) connection employing current industry standard encryption and protection practices) and permit access to such copies of the Offering solely by Education Users, only so long as the maximum number of concurrent Education Users does not exceed the permitted number of Education Users specified in the Offering Identification.<br>
<br>
<b>Educational Stand-alone (Individual) (as licensed from May 18, 2018 through August 3, 2020)</b>. If Your Education Offering is described as “Educational Stand-alone (Individual),” then You may install a copy of the specific release of the Offering designated in the applicable Offering Identification on two (2) computers (or as otherwise authorized in writing by Autodesk), and permit access to such copy of the Offering solely by Education Users. The Offering may only be installed on a single computer and may not be installed on, or operated, viewed or otherwise accessed from or through any other device (e.g., through a network connection of any kind).<br>
<br>
<b>Other Education users</b>. If Your Education Offering was licensed prior to May 18, 2018, it is subject to the terms of the applicable License and Services Agreement and the General Terms.<br>
<br>
<b>Governing Law for Public Educational Institutions</b>. If You are a Qualified Educational Institution that is majority-owned by or is a legal branch or agency of a state or local government (“<b>Public Educational Institution</b>”) located in the United States of America or Canada, then these terms related to Education Offerings (including these Terms, the General Terms, and any applicable License and Services Agreement; together, the “<b>Education Terms</b>”) will be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the state or province of the main campus for such Public Educational Institution. Such laws will govern without reference to the conflicts-of-laws rules thereof. The UN Convention on Contracts for the International Sale of Goods and the Uniform Computer Information Transaction Act will not apply to, and are excluded from the laws governing, this Agreement. Each party agrees that any claim, action or dispute arising under or relating to the Education Terms will be brought exclusively in, and the parties will be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of, the local courts of the county in which the main campus of such Public Educational Institution is located or the administrative tribunal having exclusive jurisdiction over disputes involving Public Educational Institution, as applicable.<br>
<br>
<b>Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA)</b>. Information on the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA) is available here: <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/access-use/website-terms-of-use/ferpa-terms" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="ferpa terms">https://www.autodesk.com/company/legal-notices-trademarks/access-use/website-terms-of-use/ferpa-terms</a></p>

</div>

    

</div>

    
  </div>


</div>

    
  </div>


</div>

    <div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="title-d3fe0c5d17">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
    Cloud Credits</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-9f5e10a2f3" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 ">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b><i>Cloud Credits may be required to perform certain tasks using Autodesk products, such as creating a rendering or running a simulation.</i></b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Cloud Credits</b>” are units of measure used across certain Autodesk consumption-based Web Services. You may purchase Cloud Credits or You may be granted Cloud Credits. Cloud Credits function similarly to Flex tokens, and, in most cases, Flex tokens have replaced Cloud Credits. The token rates included in the Flex Rate Sheet also apply to Cloud Credits. For more information, please see the <a></a><a href="https://www.autodesk.com/buying/flex" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="flex offering">Flex Offering page</a>.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Cloud Credit usage rates are determined by Autodesk and vary by service based on such elements as quality and size. Autodesk may change usage rates for Cloud Credits and product allocations from time to time, and the new rate is effective as of the date indicated in the Flex Rate Sheet. Cloud Credits may not be sold, bartered, traded, transferred or exchanged and will expire according to their respective attribute.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">From time to time, Autodesk may allow use of Cloud Credits beyond the allocated entitlement or designated expiration date. This does not imply continued use rights at the excess level or beyond the designated expiration date. Autodesk will charge You for any excess usage. For variable usage rates, Autodesk will endeavor to notify users of anticipated usage prior to running the service.</p>

</div>

    

</div>

</div>

</div>

<div class="experiencefragment">
<div id="experiencefragment-0600083580" class="cmp-experiencefragment cmp-experiencefragment--product-specific" data-ef-variation-path="/content/experience-fragments/autodesk/en/company/terms_of_use/en/offering_types/product-specific/master" data-ef-all-variations="master">

<div class="aem-Grid aem-Grid--12 aem-Grid--default--12 ">

  <div id="product-specific" class="cmp-container wp-parent legal-section ">
    
    <div class="core-container">

  
  
  
  
  <div id="container-11462cd238" class="cmp-container wd-mb-64 wd-bbw-1 wd-bc-smoke wd-pb-12 ">
    
    <div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="title-1f7c9d0e90">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-20 wd-mb-24">
    Product-Specific Offering Types</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="assemble">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
    Assemble</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-37491fac8e" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 wd-mb-24">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Assemble Project</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">An Assemble Project subscription entitles You and an unlimited number of Your Authorized Users to access and/or use Assemble during Your Offering Term for the applicable number of Project purchases.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Project</b>” means up to eight (8) separate buildings at one single location.  </p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Assemble Office</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">An Assemble Office subscription entitles You and an unlimited number of Your Authorized Users to access and/or use Assemble during Your Offering Term for any project within a one hundred (100)-mile radius of the physical address where the purchase of the subscription was transacted.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Assemble Region</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">An Assemble Region subscription entitles You and an unlimited number of Your Authorized Users to access and/or use Assemble during Your Offering Term for any project within a seven hundred fifty (750)-mile radius of the physical address where the purchase of the subscription was transacted.</p>

</div>

    

</div>
<div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="autodesk-construction-cloud">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
    Autodesk Construction Cloud</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-bbcb2f5d5e" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 wd-mb-24">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Autodesk Construction Cloud Connect ("Connect")</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You may use Connect to build customized, automated workflows that connect Your existing subscriptions to certain Autodesk Cloud Services with one or more third party software applications (each, a “<b>Third Party Application</b>”). In doing so, You acknowledge and agree that: (i) by using Connect, You authorize Autodesk to share Your data with Third Party Applications in connection with Connect; (ii) You are responsible for ensuring the appropriate level of access to Your data by any Third Party Application; (iii) Autodesk will have no responsibility or liability for any loss of Your data in connection with the use of Connect or for any Third Party Application or the availability thereof, and any terms and conditions, including those regarding privacy, applicable to Your use of any Third Party Application will be solely between You and the provider of such Third Party Application. At any time during the Connect Offering Term, You may activate up to two (2) authentications between Connect and available Third Party Applications (including the Autodesk Cloud Service as one such authentication). Additional authentications require the purchase of Connect Additional Endpoints and additional fees may apply. You may consume up to one million Tasks per month via Connect for each permitted authentication during the Connect Offering Term. You are not permitted to use Connect for workflows exclusively between Third Party Applications (i.e., each of Your workflows in Connect must include at least one Autodesk Cloud Service). As used in this section only, “<b>Task</b>” means each time a workflow on Connect performs an action that requires compute resources. If You exceed the Task limit, without limitation to Autodesk’s other rights and remedies under the Terms, Autodesk reserves the right to coordinate with You to optimize workflows and Autodesk may deactivate workflows that cannot be remediated. Connect is operated by a third-party platform provider (the “<b>Platform Provider</b>”). In the event the Platform Provider ceases operation of Connect for any reason, Your subscription to Connect will be subject to, at Autodesk’s sole option, either early termination or transition to an alternative platform provider.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Autodesk Construction Cloud Connect Additional Endpoints</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">In order to use this Offering, You must have a separate subscription to Autodesk Construction Cloud Connect.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Autodesk Construction Cloud Connect On-Prem Agent</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">In order to use this Offering, You must have a separate subscription to Autodesk Construction Cloud Connect.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Autodesk Construction Cloud Entitlements</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">If Your Autodesk Construction Cloud Offering includes BIM 360 Build, BIM 360 Cost, and/or PlanGrid service(s), as reflected in the applicable Autodesk order documentation, only Your Authorized User(s) who have access to Your Autodesk Construction Cloud Offering may access and use any of such service(s).</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Autodesk Construction Operations Bundle</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">The Autodesk Construction Operations Bundle includes the Autodesk Build Value-Based Offering, AutoSpecs, Pype AutoSpecs Enterprise, and Pype Closeout Enterprise.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Notwithstanding anything to the contrary in these Terms, Pype Web Services and AutoSpecs may only be accessed and used in the United States and Canada. You shall be responsible for any and all losses, liabilities, expenses (including reasonable attorneys' fees) incurred by Autodesk arising out of or relating to Your non-compliance with this limitation.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Autodesk Preconstruction Bundle</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">The Autodesk Preconstruction Bundle includes the Autodesk Takeoff Value-Based Offering, BuildingConnected BC Pro Value-Based Offering, BuildingConnected Bid Board Pro Value-Based Offering, TradeTapp Value-Based Offering, and ProEst Cloud Subscription (Unlimited) Offering.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Autodesk Model Management Bundle</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">The Autodesk Model Management Bundle includes ACC Design Collaboration, ACC Docs, ACC Model Coordination, Assemble, Autodesk Navisworks Manage, Autodesk ReCap Pro, and Autodesk Tandem for AEC.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>BuildingConnected Unique ID</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">If you are already a BuildingConnected customer, your BuildingConnected unique ID may be included with your BuildingConnected subscription.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Navisworks Manage</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">If Your Navisworks Manage Offering includes ACC Design Collaboration, Autodesk Docs or Model Coordination services, only Your Authorized User(s) who have access to Your Navisworks Manage Offering may access and use any of such services.<b></b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b style="">ProEst Costbook</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">In order to use ProEst Costbook, You must have a separate subscription to the Autodesk Preconstruction Bundle.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>TradeTapp - AXA XL</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">If You have Subcontractor Default Insurance from AXA XL as reflected in the applicable Autodesk quote or Autodesk order documentation, Your Offering includes unlimited employee accounts, and any Offering fees for TradeTapp - AXA XL are conditionally waived. If Your AXA XL Subcontractor Default Insurance policy expires or is terminated, or if Autodesk's relationship with AXA XL expires, is terminated, or is otherwise modified to remove this benefit, then Your continued access to TradeTapp will be subject to Your payment of applicable Offering fees to Autodesk at Autodesk's then-current rates, or Autodesk may terminate Your subscription to the TradeTapp Offering.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Value-Based</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">For any Value-Based Offering, the Annual Declared Value is used to determine the applicable pricing for the Value-Based Offerings. In the event that the Annual Declared Value increases during the Offering Term as a result of You being acquired or You acquiring new companies or businesses either as part of Your own business or as Subsidiaries, You will provide to Autodesk an updated Annual Declared Value, and Autodesk reserves the right to charge additional fees for the Value-Based Offerings.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">If the applicable Autodesk quote or Autodesk order documentation reflects that the Annual Declared Value for a Value-Based Offering is limited to a particular affiliate, business unit, region, project, or other limited scope, You agree to restrict Your use of the Value-Based Offering to the stated scope. You represent and warrant the accuracy of the Annual Declared Value set forth in the applicable Autodesk quote or Autodesk order documentation.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Your Authorized Users may only access and use the Value-Based Offering for work in Your account unless the Authorized User has been designated by You for use outside of Your account.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Value-Based Offerings are not subject to automatic renewal.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">For Value-Based Offerings, the following definitions apply: "<b>Project</b>" means the specific work to be planned, managed or undertaken by You or Your Subsidiaries which is, or is directly related to, the construction of a particular facility, structure or infrastructure. "<b>Project Value</b>" means the total value of a Project, including, but not limited to, the cost of all labor and materials; cost, and cost of use, of equipment; cost of architectural and engineering work; overhead costs from site survey to owner handover; interest and taxes paid during construction or other work; Your and any of Your contractor's profits; and all subcontractor and vendor costs related to a Project whether or not they are under the direct control of You or Your Subsidiaries. "<b>Annual Declared Value</b>" means, as determined by the applicable metric and scope (if any) identified in the applicable Autodesk quote or Autodesk order documentation: (i) the aggregate Project Values of all of Your Projects and the Projects of Your Subsidiaries, if Annual Declared Value is based on Your annual construction volume; (ii) the aggregate annual revenue of You and Your Subsidiaries, if Annual Declared Value is based on annual company revenue; or (iii) the aggregate annual capital budget of You and Your Subsidiaries, if Annual Declared Value is based on annual capital budget. (D) "<b>Subsidiaries</b>" means subsidiaries in which You own at least 50% of the outstanding voting shares or securities, or in jurisdictions in which 50% ownership is prohibited, effective ownership to be demonstrated by You if required.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Mid-Term Switches for Autodesk Construction Cloud</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">If you have an eligible Autodesk Construction Cloud Offering (a list of all eligible Autodesk Construction Cloud Offerings is available at <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/customer/help" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="eligible autodesk construction cloud offerings">https://www.autodesk.com/customer/help</a>) that is Single User or Value-Based, then during Your Offering Term, You may change the product included with Your Offering (a “<b>Switch</b>”) only to another Autodesk Construction Cloud product and, in conjunction with a Switch, change the length of Your Offering Term. Details related to Your Switch may be specified on Your order confirmation, or other Documentation associated with the Switch. Autodesk will inform You once Your Switch has been processed by Autodesk and takes effect. The effective date of the Switch will be referred to in this section as the “<b>Switch Date</b>.”</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You may initiate a Switch only after Your Offering is not eligible to be returned. Further, a Switch is only permitted in cases where You switch one (1) product for one (1) other product, or You switch two (2) or more products for one (1) other product. When switching one (1) product for one (1) other product, the cost of the switched-to Offering must exceed the cost of the changed-from Offering.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">When switching two (2) or more products for one (1) other product, the cost of the switched-to Offering must exceed the total cost of the changed-from Offerings. The changed-from Offering with the latest end date will be used to determine the end date of the switched-to Offering Term.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You are not permitted to switch one (1) product for two (2) or more other products, or switch two (2) or more products for two (2) or more other products.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">When You initiate a Switch, You may also change Your Offering Term. You may switch an annual subscription(s) to a multi-year subscription, or a multi-year subscription to an annual subscription. In doing so, your switched-to Offering Term will end on the latest date of Your changed-from Offering Term(s).</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">When You change one (1) or more annual subscription(s) to a multi-year subscription, Your annual subscription(s) will end on Your original subscription end date(s), and then will renew for a three (3)-year Offering Term. When You change a multi-year subscription to an annual subscription, You may only do so in the third year of Your initial multi-year subscription. Once changed, Your new annual subscription will end on Your original multi-year subscription end date, and then will renew for a one (1)-year Offering Term.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You may initiate a Switch with a future Switch Date that is no more than thirty (30) days in advance. Once You initiate a Switch, including a change to Your Offering Term, the Switch cannot be undone. Any Switch will apply to all seats included with Your Offering (e.g., if You have five (5) seats included with Your changed-from subscription, all five (5) seats will be subject to the Switch).</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You will be able to access both the changed-from product(s) and the switched-to product for fifteen (15) days after the Switch Date. However, You are not permitted to access the changed-from product(s) and switched-to product concurrently during this fifteen (15)-day period. Upon fifteen (15) calendar days following the Switch Date, all Offering benefits of the changed-from Offering(s) (the “<b>Original Offering Benefits</b>”) will terminate. After such termination, except as noted in any additional terms and conditions applicable to Your switched-to Offering, (a) You must cease all use of any Original Offering Benefits, and (b) You will no longer have the right to access or otherwise use any such Original Offering Benefits. At Autodesk’s request, You agree to uninstall and destroy or return to Autodesk or the reseller from which they were acquired all copies of the Original Offering Benefits and, on request, show satisfactory proof that all copies of any Original Offering Benefits have been uninstalled and destroyed or returned to Autodesk or the reseller from which they were acquired.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Any amounts pre-paid for the remainder of the changed-from Offering Term(s) will be applied as daily pro-rated credit as of the Switch Date to the cost of the switched-to Offering Term during the then-current open billing period (e.g., if You have a multi-year Offering Term and Switch during year 2, the pro-rated credit, if any, would apply to Your year 2 billing). Any unbilled amounts for your changed-from Offering(s) will be canceled upon the Switch Date. Any renewal of Your switched-to Offering Term will be priced at renewal.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">You may change Your payment method when performing a Switch, but the cost of the switched-to Offering will remain in the same currency as the currency in which You transacted with Autodesk before the Switch. However, if You fail to pay any amounts owed, then Your switched-to Offering will be terminated for non-payment, the changed-from Offering will not be reactivated, and any daily pro-rated credit will be forfeited. Notwithstanding anything to the contrary elsewhere in these Terms of Use, any switched-to Offerings are not eligible to be returned for a refund.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Any Offerings that You may Switch during Your Offering Term are not eligible for a renewal discount until You renew such Offerings for a subsequent Offering Term, and any discounts that You may receive in connection with an Autodesk trade-in program (e.g., TTN, M2S, and I2S) will terminate upon the Switch Date.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Only Offerings purchased via the Autodesk new buying experience are eligible to Switch, and this excludes the following Offerings and subscription types: Flex Offerings, Premium, and monthly subscriptions. Other terms and conditions may apply. All Switches are subject to Autodesk approval.</p>

</div>

    

</div>
<div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="forma">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
    Autodesk Forma</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-b712daf884" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 wd-mb-24">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Notwithstanding anything contained in these Terms or in the General Terms, when the term of Your paid Autodesk Forma subscription expires or terminates, all of Your Authorized Users will be converted automatically to Viewers, and Autodesk will continue to store Your Content so that it remains accessible in Autodesk Forma to Viewers on the conditions described below. Such access to Autodesk Forma remains subject to these Terms.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Upon the expiration or termination of Your paid Autodesk Forma subscription, (i) so long as You are in compliance with these Terms, Autodesk will stop storing Your Content only upon advance notice to You, and (ii) otherwise, Autodesk may delete, without notice, any or all of Your Content, including backup and other copies thereof. This convenience does not relieve You of the responsibility for retaining and securing complete copies of Your Content at all times.</p>

</div>

    

</div>
<div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="fusion">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
    Autodesk Fusion</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-dd8df3c2f3" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 wd-mb-24">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Autodesk Fusion is available for startups. For more information, including who may qualify and how to apply, see here: <a href="https://www.autodesk.com/campaigns/fusion-360/startups" data-wat-link="true" data-wat-loc="content" data-wat-val="f360 startups">https://www.autodesk.com/campaigns/fusion-360/startups</a>.<b></b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Fusion Content Storage Standard</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">If your Fusion subscription has ended, Your Content created and stored in Fusion Hubs (“Fusion Content”) will remain accessible to you for a period of 365 days from the date your subscription ends or your account becomes inactive. After such time, your Fusion Content may no longer be accessible. Certain restrictions apply – see the chart below. These procedures apply only to Your Fusion Content stored within a Fusion Hub in the following Offerings: Autodesk Fusion, Autodesk Fusion Extensions, and Autodesk Fusion Team.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">These procedures do not apply to Education users.</p>
<table cellspacing="2" cellpadding="8" border="1">
<tbody><tr><td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Fusion Customer Subscription Type</b></p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Inactive Status</b></p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Storage Period</b></p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Re-gaining Active Status</b></p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Commercial, Start-Up, and Trial</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Your Fusion Content and Fusion Hub are considered inactive once Your subscription is terminated or expired.</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Your inactive Fusion Content will be accessible to You for 365 days in <a href="https://help.autodesk.com/view/fusion360/ENU/?guid=GS-BASIC-ACCESS" target="_blank">Basic Access</a> mode after the termination or expiration of Your subscription.</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Resubscribe to your Fusion subscription (renew or repurchase) within the retention period.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Personal Use</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Your Fusion Content and Fusion Hub are considered inactive if you have not logged into Fusion for more than 365 consecutive days.</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">365 consecutive inactive days.</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Keep your verified Personal Use subscription and log into Fusion at least once every 365 days.</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Shared Hub: Any combination of the subscription types above, operating and collaborating in one Fusion Hub</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Your Fusion Content and Fusion Hub are considered inactive only when all users in the shared Fusion Hub are inactive.</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">365 days of inactive status from all team members in the shared Fusion Hub.</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">A team member can re-gain their active status (in the subscription types above) which will re-gain active status for such a Fusion Hub.</p>
</td>
</tr></tbody></table>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Autodesk reserves the right to modify this Fusion Content Storage Standard from time to time.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Learn More:</b></p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><a href="https://www.autodesk.com/support/technical/article/caas/sfdcarticles/sfdcarticles/FAQ-for-Fusion-Content-Storage-Standard.html">Fusion Content Storage Standard: how it works</a></p>

</div>

    

</div>

<div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="design">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
    Autodesk Informed Design</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-9dbfc3b1b0" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 ">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Autodesk Informed Design is available for Single User, Flex and Token Flex offerings.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">In order to access Autodesk Informed Design, you must meet the following criteria: (i) you must have a subscription to Autodesk Docs, and (ii) you must have a positive token balance.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">For the initial access period, users can create up to 5,000 free outputs a month.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“Outputs” means a drawing, bill of materials, CAD model* or other data derived from a specific instance of a building product template placed in a building project.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">*Neutral formats for CAD model outputs currently include .sat, .step, .glb, and .stl.</p>

</div>

    

</div>
<div class="title">
<div class="cmp-title" id="tandem">
  <h3 class="cmp-title__text pc-brand wd-font-18">
    Autodesk Tandem</h3>
</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-90e5a350ed" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 wd-mb-24">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Subscriptions to Autodesk Tandem, including the Autodesk Tandem for AEC Offering, are tiered based on the number of Tagged Assets, Streams, length of Time Series History, and user type as described below.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">The free and standard Offerings entitle You to (a) designate an unlimited number of Users, and (b) use Autodesk Tandem with an unlimited number of Facilities.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">The Autodesk Tandem for AEC Offering is available as an entitlement for Autodesk BIM Collaborate Pro paid subscribers. Autodesk Tandem for AEC includes, per subscription, one (1) User, a fourteen (14)-day time series history, and an unlimited number of Facilities, Tagged Assets, and Streams.</p>
<table cellspacing="2" cellpadding="8" border="1">
<tbody><tr><td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Subscription Tier</b></p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Free<sup>1</sup></b></p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Standard<sup>2</sup></b></p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Autodesk Tandem for AEC<sup>3</sup></b></p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Number of Tagged Assets</b></p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">1,000 or less</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">10,000/pack</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Unlimited</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Number of Streams</b></p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">200 or less </p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">2,000/pack </p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Unlimited</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Time Series History</b></p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">14 days</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">3 years</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">14 days</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Users</b></p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Unlimited</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Unlimited</p>
</td>
<td valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">1 per subscription</p>
</td>
</tr><tr><td colspan="4" valign="top"><p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">1. available with a limited set of features and permitted for use for Your internal business needs, subject to change or termination by Autodesk at any time without notice</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">2. includes the same set of features, entitlements, and conditions as the Free subscription, but with 10,000 Tagged Assets per pack and 2,000 Streams per pack</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">3. available as a free entitlement for Autodesk BIM Collaborate Pro paid subscribers, subject to change or termination by Autodesk at any time without notice</p>
</td>
</tr></tbody></table>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Autodesk Tandem and Autodesk Tandem for AEC are also available as standalone Offerings for EBA customers. For such EBA customers, the terms included in this section do not apply. Instead, the Autodesk Tandem and/or Autodesk Tandem for AEC terms included in Your EBA will apply.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Use Limit</b>: You can view and monitor Your usage within Autodesk Tandem. If Your usage of Autodesk Tandem exceeds the subscription tier limit of Your purchase, You should either promptly remove such unauthorized Tagged Assets or Streams or issue a purchase order or signed quote to Autodesk within a reasonable time (no more than thirty (30) calendar days from the date of first overage) to purchase additional subscriptions. Overage constitutes a material breach of these Terms.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">Any reference to “unlimited” usage in these Terms is subject to reasonable technical limitations, which Autodesk has the sole discretion to impose at any time without notice.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Element</b>” means any object imported into Autodesk Tandem from a data source, which may be physical elements such as walls, doors, windows, equipment, light fixtures, furniture, etc. or logical elements such as types, rooms, levels, etc.  </p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">“<b>Tagged Asset</b>” means any Element that has an asset type specified and additional asset data attached via the use of Autodesk Tandem. Elements<b> </b>that contain only data imported from the data source are not counted as Tagged Asset.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>“Streams”</b> means the data points or readings such as temperature and vibration that come from the connection of a physical device or sensor in Autodesk Tandem and are recorded at a user-defined frequency then stored for a specific retention period (<b>time series history</b>). For free Offering subscriptions, the time series history is fourteen (14) days. For Standard Offering subscriptions, the time series history is three (3) years.  For Autodesk Tandem for AEC, the time series history is fourteen (14) days.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>“Facilities”</b> means digital twins in Autodesk Tandem that are created by importing one or more data sources, such as Revit files, IFC files, or other supported design formats.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>“User”</b> means any Authorized User added to an account with “Read”, “Edit”, “Manage”, or “Account Admin” permission, or any Authorized User added to a Facility with “Read”, “Edit” or “Manage” permission.</p>

</div>

    

</div>
<div class="text">
<div id="text-dbf8cc3aa1" class="cmp-text cmp-text-v2 wd-mb-24">
  <p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12"><b>Autodesk Tandem Connect</b>   </p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">The free and standard Autodesk Tandem Connect Offerings are available as entitlements for Autodesk Tandem customers and are tiered based on the number of Plugins and MQTT Brokers as described below. The Autodesk Tandem Connect Offerings are not available for Autodesk Tandem for AEC customers.</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">The free and standard Offerings entitle you to designate an unlimited number of Users and Sandbox Pipelines. The standard Offering enables Production Pipelines to either run in the cloud for connecting to cloud-based enterprise solutions, or behind a customer’s firewall for connecting to control systems, and on-premises enterprise solutions.</p>

<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">2. as an add-on to Autodesk Tandem, includes the same set of features, entitlements, and conditions as the Free subscription tier, but with 10 Plugins in Production Pipelines per pack and with one (1) MQTT Broker per pack included with the MQTT Broker add-on</p>
<p class="wd-font-14 wd-mv-12">3. Autodesk Tandem Connect MQ is an add-on to the Tandem Connect Standard Offering which provides an MQTT Broker. The MQTT Broker add-on is not available for the Autodesk Tandem Connect Free Offering</p>
